            "id": "4449270",
            "title": "OFS Credit Company lowers April NAV per share estimate range",
            "description": "<html><body><p>Collateralized loan obligation investment company OFS Credit Company (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\">NASDAQ:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/OCCI\" title=\"OFS Credit Company Inc\">OCCI</a></span>) <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/pr/20106835-ofs-credit-company-announces-preliminary-estimates-of-certain-financial-results-for-its\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"announced\">announced</a> on Thursday a lower range of its unaudited NAV per share estimate for April.</p>\n<p>The estimate is between $6.12 and $6.22 as of April 30. Comparatively, the March estimate stood at $6.57-$6.67.</p>\n<p>The unaudited range of NII per share estimate for the quarter ended April 30 is between $0.19 and $0.23. As of April 30, the company had $115.9M of term preferred stock outstanding.</p>\n</body></html>",
            "image": "https://static.seekingalpha.com/assets/og_image_1200-29b2bfe1a595477db6826bd2126c63ac2091efb7ec76347a8e7f81ba17e3de6c.png",
