            "id": "4449274",
            "title": "Paulson & Co takes new stake in Honeywell in Q1",
            "description": "<html><body><p class=\"MsoNormal\">Paulson &amp; Co, the hedge fund founded by John Paulson, takes a new stake in diversified industrial giant Honeywell International (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\">NASDAQ:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/HON\" title=\"Honeywell International Inc.\">HON</a></span>) in the first quarter, according to its latest <a href=\"https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/1035674/000101359425000679/xslForm13F_X02/informationtable.xml\" rel=\"nofollow\">13F filing</a> submitted on Thursday.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">During the quarter, the fund boosted its stakes in Madrigal Pharmaceuticals (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/MDGL\" title=\"Madrigal Pharmaceuticals, Inc.\">MDGL</a>) to 2.1 million shares from 2 million, while it raised its position to 70.24 million shares from 64.2 million shares in International Tower Hill Mines (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/THM\" title=\"International Tower Hill Mines Ltd.\">THM</a>).</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Apart from the new 200K shares in Honeywell, the fund also took a new stake of 21.5K shares in biopharmaceutical company Intra-Cellular Therapies (ITCI).</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Meanwhile, Paulson closed out its position in Alphabet Class A shares (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/GOOGL\" title=\"Alphabet Inc.\">GOOGL</a>).</p>\n</body></html>",
            "image": "https://static.seekingalpha.com/assets/og_image_1200-29b2bfe1a595477db6826bd2126c63ac2091efb7ec76347a8e7f81ba17e3de6c.png",
            "link": "https://seekingalpha.com/news/4449274-paulson-co-takes-new-stake-in-honeywell-in-q1",
            "pub_date": "2025-05-16 05:21:26",
            "source": "seekalpha",
