            "id": "4449187",
            "title": "Third Point adds US Steel, Kenvue, exits Danaher, Tesla among Q1 moves",
            "description": "<html><body><p>Dan Loeb's Third Point added new positions in US Steel (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\">NYSE:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/X\" title=\"United States Steel Corporation\">X</a></span>) and Nvidia in Q1, while exiting stakes in Danaher (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\">NYSE:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/DHR\" title=\"Danaher Corporation\">DHR</a></span>) and Tesla (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\">NASDAQ:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/TSLA\" title=\"Tesla, Inc.\">TSLA</a></span>), according to its latest 13F filing. </p>\n<p>The activist hedge fund purchased 3.63m shares of US Steel (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\">NYSE:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/X\" title=\"United States Steel Corporation\">X</a></span>) in Q1, as well as new position in Kenvue (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/KVUE\" title=\"Kenvue Inc.\">KVUE</a>) +8.9m , Nvidia +1.45m, Casey's General Stores (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/CASY\" title=\"Casey's General Stores, Inc.\">CASY</a>) and CoStar (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/CSGP\" title=\"CoStar Group, Inc.\">CSGP</a>), according to the<a href=\"https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/1040273/000108514625003337/xslForm13F_X02/infotable.xml\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" title=\" filing \"> filing </a> on Thursday. </p>\n<p>Third Point exited stakes in Danaher (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\">NYSE:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/DHR\" title=\"Danaher Corporation\">DHR</a></span>), selling off 1.9m, Meta (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/META\" title=\"Meta Platforms, Inc.\">META</a>), Ferguson (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/FERG\" title=\"Ferguson Enterprises Inc.\">FERG</a>) and Thermo Fisher (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/TMO\" title=\"Thermo Fisher Scientific Inc.\">TMO</a>) and Tesla (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\">NASDAQ:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/TSLA\" title=\"Tesla, Inc.\">TSLA</a></span>).</p>\n<p>The fund also increased its stake in Apollo Global (APOL), Live Nation (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/LYV\" title=\"Live Nation Entertainment, Inc.\">LYV</a>) and Telephone and Data Systems (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/TDS\" title=\"Telephone and Data Systems, Inc.\">TDS</a>). Third Point reduced its stake in Amazon (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/AMZN\" title=\"Amazon.com, Inc.\">AMZN</a>), Microsoft (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/MSFT\" title=\"Microsoft Corporation\">MSFT</a>) and Intercontinental Exchange (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/ICE\" title=\"Intercontinental Exchange, Inc.\">ICE</a>).</p>\n</body></html>",
            "image": "https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1192097505/image_1192097505.jpg?io=getty-c-w750",
